<div class="container">
    <h1 align="center">About GiraffeSpotter</h1>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="panel panel-gold" align="center" style="border-color: #636363;">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3>What is GiraffeSpotter?</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>It is an online platform for Citizen Science.</p>
                    
                    <p>Simply put, <strong>GiraffeSpotter</strong> is a platform to help giraffe science and conservation in Africa.</p>
                    
                    <p><strong>GiraffeSpotter</strong> harnesses the power of ‘citizen scientists’ – anyone, anywhere in Africa who sees a giraffe in the wild can help to improve our understanding of these large megafauna and to protect them.</p>
                    <br />
                    
                    <div class="thumbnail">
                        <img src="~/Images/GS_Spotter_Finals_no_web2.jpg" height="100" width="180"/>
                    </div>
                   <br />
                    <br />
                   
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="panel panel-gold" align="center" style="border-color: #636363;">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h3>Anyone can join</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p>
                        Anyone can  <a target="_blank" href="~/Account/Register">join</a> <strong>GiraffeSpotter</strong>. Whether you are a game guard, a tour guide, a farm owner or worker, 
                   a scientist, a giraffe enthusiast or a tourist on an African safari, you can upload your <a target="_blank" href="~/Gallery/GalleryView">photos</a> and observations to <strong>GiraffeSpotter</strong>. You can help spread the message about the plight of giraffe in Africa. 
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                        Scientists from GCF and giraffe experts from around the world will use your information to better understand giraffe distribution and numbers. We will use this knowledge to improve giraffe conservation efforts in Africa.<br /><br />
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="thumbnail">
                         <img src="~/Images/group-of-people.jpg"  height="100" width="180" />
                    </div>
                    <br />
                   
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="panel panel-gold" align="center" style="border-color: #636363;">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h4>A Community of Citizen Scientists and Conservationists</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <p><strong>GiraffeSpotter</strong> is more than just a website. </p>
                    
                    <p>It is a community of citizen scientists and conservationists with the common goal to protect giraffe in their natural habitat and increase our knowledge of the tallest of all mammals.</p>
                    <br /><br /><br />
                    <br />
